$ Registry: HKEY_CLASSES_ROOT\SystemFileAssociations

The registry key `HKEY_CLASSES_ROOT\SystemFileAssociations` guarantees that Shell extensions are installed regardless of the current default
→ Windows/registry/tree/HKEY_CLASSES_ROOT/ProgId[ProgID] or user customization and define fallback attributes for file types and enable shared file associations.

? Subkeys allow to define behavior of attributes and enable shared file associations for file types.

{ Registry keys for perceived types

  `HKEY_CLASSES_ROOT\SystemFileAssociations` also contains the → Windows/registry/tree-structure/key[keys] for *perceived types* such as
    • `audio`
    • `compressed` (?)
    • `document`
    • `image`
    • `text`
    • `system`
    • `video`

  A *perceived type* differs from a *specific type* in that the perceived type refers to a category of file format types.

}
sa:
  → Windows/registry/tree/HKEY_CLASSES_ROOT/_ext[`HKEY_CLASSES_ROOT\.ext`]
